The paper discusses the identification of influential nodes in a network for viral marketing, which falls under the category of social networks. Therefore, cs.SOC is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an algorithm for identifying these nodes, which involves computational modeling and simulations, indicating that it could also belong to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of network metrics and topological features suggests that it could also belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper uses a Susceptible-Infected-Recovered model for simulations, which is a common approach in the study of epidemics and disease spread, indicating that it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
